question:
Consider the following statements: 
S1:  If $A$ is a $4 \times 4$ matrix such that $\mathrm{det}=-2$, then $\mathrm{det} \left( 2 A^T A^{-1} \right)=16$; 
S2: Let $A$ be an $m \times n$ matrix. If the equation $A\textbf{x}=\textbf{0}$ has only the trivial solution $x \in \mathbb{R}^n$, then the columns of $A$ are linearly independent.

Find $x$ and $y$ such that $\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-2 & 1 \\ 
3 & -4 \end{array}
\right)\left( \begin{array}{rr}
x & 2 \\ 
1 & y \end{array}
\right)=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-3 & 1 \\ 
2 & -14 \end{array}
\right)$.

Suppose that $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
2 & 0 & -1 \\ 
3 & 1 & 0 \\ 
-2 & 1 & 3 \end{array}
\right)$.

Find matrix $B$ such that matrices $A$ and $B$ are inverses.

Let $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
-1 & 2 & 0 \\ 
2 & -4 & 0 \end{array}
\right)$. Which of the following statements is correct?

